                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d234">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/1014.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-07-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 25, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>As long as the other Governments concerned do likewise, the Department must
                    adhere to the position stated in the instruction to you dated July 2. In other
                    respects the company must use its own discretion.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
